#### system ####

uname -a    == shows the information of the system (system name version and all info)

hostname   == system name only 

uname -r   == show kernal release info.

hostname -i  == show ip of system / ip a

last reboot  == show history of reboot

date ,cal   

.......................................

### HARDWARE ###

free -m   == show use memory 

cat /proc/cpuinfo  == CPU model (processer all details )

cat /proc/meminfo  == memory information in details

lshw  == system hardware info.

lsusb -tv  == show USB devices

.....................................

### NETWORK ###

dig domain  == get DNS information for domain

dig -x host == reverse lookup host (same info as above...)

host google.com  == show DNS ip adress for the name (ip and ipv6 for name )

wget file    / yum install file /  download file 

ping host  == send echo request to the test connection

~ netstat -tupl == list active connection to / from system

    ifconfig -a  == show all network ports and ip adress


.......................

